Sentencas: The volt-ampere and impedance characteristics of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) at 800 degrees C depending on the structure of the anode, electrolyte, and cathode were studied.
Titulo: The Influence of the Anode Structure on the Electrical Properties of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The combination of the 10Sc1CeSZ-NiO anode with the 10Sc1CeSZ electrolyte, the GDC barrier cathode layer, and the LSCF-GDC cathode leads to an increase in the electrical properties of this SOFC in 1.4 and 2.8 times compared to the SOFC of the 3.5YSZ-NiO/8YSZ/LSM-8YSZ system to the SOFC of the 10Sc1CeSZ-NiO/8YSZ/LSM-8YSZ system, respectively.
Titulo: The Influence of the Anode Structure on the Electrical Properties of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: At the same time, the incompatibility of the 10Sc1CeSZ-NiO anode and the 8YSZ electrolyte was revealed, which is associated with cerium migration during sintering of the half-cell.
Titulo: The Influence of the Anode Structure on the Electrical Properties of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
